🌟 What is pathlib?

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔹 Definition

```text id="pathlib_def"
pathlib is a modern, object-oriented module for handling file system paths.
```

---

🎯 Why pathlib?

✔ Cleaner syntax
✔ Cross-platform support
✔ Easier path handling
✔ Recommended in modern Python

---

📥 Import pathlib

```python id="import_pathlib"
from pathlib import Path
```

---

📂 Create Path Object

---

💻 Example

```python id="path_object"
from pathlib import Path

path = Path("data.txt")

print(path)
```

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔍 Check File Exists

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

💻 Example

```python id="path_exists"
